  "doc_id": "40409",
  "text": "In rodent skeletal muscle, experimentally elevated circulating free fatty acids increased intracellular acetyl-CoA and DAG levels which was coupled to increased active protein kinase C (PKC) theta. These changes were accompanied by increased IRS-1 serine phosphorylation, reduced IRS-1 tyrosine phosphorylation and reduced IRS-1 associated PI3K activity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Phosphorylation of IRS-1 at serine 307 evidently hinders IRS-1's interaction with PI3K and therefore interferes with normal insulin signalling.",
